title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.4: SOCIAL POLICY AND CHILD FRIENDLY BUDGETING

description.narrative: Output 4.4: National and county actors are able to plan, budget, monitor and track expenditures, as well as leverage resources to scale-up evidence-based, innovative and risk-informed approaches to fulfilling children's and adolescents' rights, which contributes to Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 4 - Social inclusion: An increased number of children from the poorest & most vulnerable households benefit from shock- responsive & integrated social protection interventions, as well as from child-specific policies

description.narrative: UNICEF's strategic partnership with Government of Kenya (GoK) and key Public Finance Management (PFM) partners, combined with strategic advocacy and Government capacity building on Public Finance for Children(PF4C) has resulted in an improved positioning of children's rights in budget and plans.
